The Catholic Shrine in Little Mount is a part of Chennai's history.
The hillock encompasses a cave, where St. Thomas would hide from his enemies. The miraclous spring which sustained him during his stay is still yielding water.
There are many relics associated with him.
A new garden with the stations of the cross has been just installed. It will make a pilgrimage complete.

You can access the church by steps, or drive up, but watch out for the narrow road,  lest you miss it.
A must for every first time visitor.

It is historical Catholics Church. It is under Madras Mylapore Dioceses. Excellent place to visit. Everyone have to visit in their life time at least one time. Attached images are neweley created the way of the Jesus and 12th station of historical way of cross.
I am having severe arthritis but  by the grace of God, I  managed to climb the stairs on my knees. Praise the Lord.  Alleluia.  Amen.

Good place for praying. Visiting inside St. Thomas cave was a very chilling spiritual experience. Must visit when you are in Chennai as it tells about 2000 years old christian faith in India specially in Chennai, Tamil Nadu.

Beautiful church. Very historical place Not only for Indian church history but also of global significance. 
A center for Family ministry and also youth activities.

Any NGO is there?? One of my friend's uncle who have been lost since 2012 is found on an NGO." St Holy cross " has writeen over the tshirt of that NGO. So i just want to confirm is there any link between that ngo or this church??. If any one knows something about that church or  ngo plz contact me.

Hello All, I am visitor from Kolkata and will be in Chennai on Sunday 25th March,2018 which is Palm Sunday, I would be staying in Cenotaph Road, in-front of Moopnar Flyover, Can some one please let me know as to which Catholic Church is near to this place and I can attend the Service in the Evening please

Super spacious. Buffet system also more space.  In my visit first time only in my life.  Because I am Hindu but my friends more in Christian. I went for my friends get together. One of the old and best church in Chennai. Must visit and pray. Well maintained. Lot of parking space. Regular bible study. I love this church

Tranquil in the midst of commotion! If you are familiar with Dome of the Rock in Jerusalem, then this would feel like Dome of the Rock in Chennai! Egmore railway station, Metro Rail, and bus depot nearby. It is gated. Expect the security personnel to ask the purpose of your visit, if there's no event going on. 

I have attended Tuesday evening Bible Study Fellowship here. It is conducted from mid-August to mid-April.

Beautiful place to worship in town. A perfect place to hear the True Word of God. Church filled with humble and true servants of God. Must try for any resident in town and tourists. Sunday worship services are at 7 AM, 9 AM and 6 PM. Pipe Organ in this church is iconic and a historical treasure that adds to the beauty of this sanctuary.
Its a very beautiful church with plenty of history . Service is lively and the pastors r very good. Songs and worship is traditional but incorpirating the modern trend of worship

St.Georges cathedral one of the oldest church in Chennai built in 1815.

It's so beautifully built and Well maintained it has the oldest organ too.

Best place for a wedding. It has different services 

The congregation have there owned funeral area.

Spacious car and bike parking.

It's one of the grandest church I've seen in chennai

The Cathedral is over 200 years old but with one coat of paint it will look like it was built only yesterday because it is well maintained - the lawns aren't maintained as much though. I can't say that the Cathedral is beautiful but There's so much character in the Cathedral. It looks so grand. There are plaques to commemorate people who have passed away -on the walls right from the entrance till the end of the prayer hall. It is quite interesting to read them all - each plaque offers a glimpse into the life of that person being remembered. You will also find plaques commemorating British Officers who were murdered during the Freedom Struggle by Rebel Freedom Fighters. You can say that the walls are almost like a mini museum. The vintage furniture too looks like it has been there for very long but it is solid - I never found them creaking. You could get lost just by looking at it and being in it. It calms your nerves.

Requires a good amount of maintenance. Lacklustre service.

Stayed in the guest house located in the  premises of St. Marrhias' Church. The guest is well maintained and given for a very reasonable rent. Air-conditioned rooms with refrigerator, television and geyser are amenities provided. The staff are very courteous and helpful. There is a school also in the same premises. The compound is quite spacious and big. It's heartening to see CSI is maintaining the facilities  for the use of community.
Ok nice church..
Hope it stays put for a few more centuries :)
Good church with room facilities

Very beautiful church. Good P.A system. Enough parking place. but very hard to identify on the road with the normal traffic. Located next to HBI.

Excellent church in Kilpauk circle, real reformed doctrines, if you want to grow in bible study and fellowship this is the right church. So may fellowships it has, Senior Citizen, Men's fellowship, Women's fellowship, Young mother fellowship, couples fellow-ship, Young adults, teens Fellowship, Sunday schools. Also this church involved in various ministries like Sunday schools and Teens fellowships in the nearby area almost more than 12 places its is conducting Sunday schools,Teens fellowships and prayer cells among Hindu brothers and sisters. I really thank God for being a part in the church.

Nice atmosphere

it's very peaceful here,

One among Historical places of Jain Temple,

One of the Finest And the Oldest Jain Temple in Chennai.

Very old JAIN temple. Having approximately 2500 years old lord adeswar Bhagwan murti. Good place of worship. Nearly 1000 people visit every Sunday. And nearly 3000 people visit on Purnima’s.  A temple of Sri Shankhswar Parshwanath is also built with full marbles. A good Dharamshala is also available for devotees. Food facilities is also available for devotees . Big functions such as updhan for devotees is usually done here for easy ness . On big occasions such as updhan or Akshay tritiya their use to be a gathering of 5000 to6000 people
Very important and very pleasant place.  Best time to visit. 6am to8 am. And evening 5pm to7pm.  You can see good view

Ashtalakshmi Temple, a delightful and soft coloured temple complex, is located in Besant Nagar, in the South Indian state of Chennai. The temple complex is built a few meters away from the Besant beach on the coast of the gorgeous Bay of Bengal. Ashtalakshmi, the Goddess of Wealth and Knowledge resides here and blesses everyone who visits the temple to offer their prayers with a clean soul. Soak in the divine ambience of the temple on the scenic coast of Bay of Bengal and observe the colourful and intricate tiers on the shrines. The serenity is unquestionable and sure to calm jittery nerves of the pilgrims and devotees. Apart from locals, you can also witness tourists flocking in from different parts of the world to enjoy the mesmerizing beauty of the temple.

Ashtalakshmi temple is one of very famous in Chennai. It's located on the sea shore in Besant Nagar. Very nice temple with beautiful architecture and has very good views. This temple is for Goddess Lakshmi and her eight forms. Parking area is available.

It is a temple dedicated to Goddess Lakshmi and her eight forms. Each deity here is very beautifully adorned and makes us feel blessed. Situated in a picturesque location, this temple is constructed in a different style than most other South Indian temples.

A peaceful sacred temple dedicated specifically to the Goddess Lakshmi.. Lord Vishnu is also worshipped here.. Temple located near the sea shore adding even more attraction to the temple.. Very peaceful place to spend the devotional time with family.. Loving it..

One of the best place I have ever been to. It was extremely quite and a pleasant ambience. There were a lot of beautiful painitings which portrayed old epic stories. I don't go to temples much but I felt extremely relaxed once I came back from there and wished to visit the place often.There is a huge parking space. I would recommend this place for anyone who is in the pursuit of peace. It's best to go on weekdays as there will be less crowd so that you can enjoy the place at it's best!!!!!!

This one is a must visit if you are in Chennai or have come to visit Chennai. Beautiful temple, much beautiful are the idols and the environment is so serene. 
Even after you leave the place "Hare Krishna Hare Rama" will keep reverberating in your ears !! You can get great prasad and other paid food items too!

I visited this place during Aarti time. This is a Chennai branch of world famous ISKCON faith which worships Krishna. This place is spiritual and you can seat, pray and meditate here. You will find many books of the philosophy which you may find useful. The place has an attached Snacks & Restaurant place.

This is one of the best spiritual place. This place is very neat and calm. The best place for good vibes in this location.  But this place is getting little crowded these days . Worth visiting this place in non busy timings.we can spend time in exploring the beauty of the place in the first visit. Most of it is built with white marble and place looks fabulous with colorful lights. 
Overall best place for good vibes and spirituality

It's an interesting thing about the Temple. The restroom isn't free, it's 5 rupees. For ISKCON temple it's not appropriate. BUT if you're taking money for restroom at least Clean it properly. Water is everywhere on the floor. Barefoot walking on this water in the restroom. In this water is urine drops of course, multiplying bacteria and fungi, etc. It's totally Karmic restroom. 
The authorities of the temple do not understand where they are and do not understand what they are doing? Where is the ISKCON Standards? 
For the temple it is indecently dirty. In the temple there are many membranes who sacrifice big money on the deities and to the temple. And even they need to pay money to go to such a dirty toilet?

One of the oldest temple in Chennai. It was in Secretariat during British period and Great Marathi warrior Shivaji worshipped Goddess Kaalikambal. No proper parking facility. Goddess Kaalikambal is very beautiful .
One of the oldest temple in Chennai. We could feel the vibe when we enter sanctum.  Mostly crowded. I am visiting this temple almost for 3 decades. I experience the vibe whenever I visit this temple.
Located near washermanpet metro. Easily accessible but narrow roads. Reaching by two Wheeler, auto cab preferred. Quite and peaceful place inside a crowded market area. Visit and get blessed...

Very calm, serene and soothing place. On way to main deity there is a pillar having lots of religious value -and is traditionally circumnavigated.
Entry is through congested place. Besides no parking and it is one way road. So has to be planned accordingly and timed.
Overall a great experience.

Yes congested for parking but two wheelers can be parked. Nice temple . Route will be confused if you don't use google map. 
The feel of praying in this temple is good.You may feel more spiritual.
No disturbance from outsiders very calm place.
Getting vehicles nearby is very difficult. Sorrunded by market. Otherwise it's a good temple.
A 300 to 400 years old Murugan as Kandasamy temple ...which was sung by Sri Pamban Swamikal
Lord Murugan temple..Good place to pray
The temple which is very old. Proud to our locality. Land mark for Kosapet
Peaceful place and I like visiting this temple every day

Wonderful and soulful place to visit. The different avatars of Multiple Gods were the main attraction for me including the marvelous structure of the temple. On the day I visited the place there was a function going on there this made my visit more special. N.B- PLEASE DON'T PUT YOUR SHOES OUTSIDE THE TEMPLE UNATTENDED. Cause you will lose it(Like I did).

Nice temple big one. Water and parking facility is good. Temple also maintained well. Very famous and 3500 yrs old mango tree is there. Better visit before 10 or after evening. Because it's too hot outside temple to walk without chappal. But inside you won't feel that much hot. You can spend more time there. I love it

Love to visit this temple always..  Calm and serene..  Go early morning for darshanam..  Loads of restaurants around to finish off a wonderful breakfast and head start your day..   The flower shops around add to the color and vibrancy of the place..

Stunning temple. Beware 'guides'  who offer to take you around small fee for using a camera - phone cameras are free. Huge impressive tank at back of complex. Non Hindus not allowed inside inner temple building
Positive vibes that you feel the moment you enter the compound. Nice architecture. cats and cows chilling on the premises. What more can you ask? Experience divinity
Beautiful Lord Muruga is sitting on top of hill temple. Even senior citizens can clime up hill. Evening will be pleasant to enjoy sweet breeze and holy atmosphere

Widely and rightly known as Kumaran Kundram-Lord Kumaran with his Grace and Unique Beauty blesses every devotee from this Small Hilltop(Kundru) in a Standing pose... At nights one can see the entire view of Chromepet which dazzles in night lights.. Applause to the Temple admin and authority for it's neat maintenance..
Very good place... Divine and peaceful.... Some renovation is happening in the entrance. 100 + steps. Had a good time.
Wonderful Murugan temple on a small hill ..nice place to visit in Chennai.. go in evening for nice cool breeze
It's very nice and located with small hills.  We  can enjoy and divine with peace atmosphere

Nostalgic place.. brings back old memories whenever I cross this beautiful temple.. even more beautiful was the huge tree adjacent to the temple premises-which used to be an icon for so many years.. pity, it was cut down as there was no sign of life in it.. however the temple offers its deities the peace of mind they are searching for and it will continue to be one of the famous cultural landmarks of Chennai city!

Centrally located and easily accessible from bus stop and by car. Road side parking is available. Slippers have to be kept near the temple entrance and there is nobody to take care. New pairs will get lost very easily and you can never spot anyone to question particularly at night times.
My fav destination which brings in find memories of my friend... Good temple.. devoted staffs

Its a nice temple in Chennai. Very calm and pleasant place. Worth watching it. Its Lord Vinayaka Temple. Has a lot of buses to reach the temple. Temple is located at a busy road. Its Near to Thiruvanmayur Railway station also.
Calm atmosphere. It was one of the best temples I have visited I saw various New avathars of the god and got a great experience.

One of the oldest Baba temples in the city and now renovated to a big level. Bit more spacious now on the inside. Neatly planned. One can always find high amounts of people in here. The temple itself is pretty well maintained with tile and granite flooring mixed. Nice ventilation as well with air-conditioning. The area behind the main Baba statue is maintained well too, the place were the holy tree and and two halls are present. The one hall in the bottom has one more Baba statue, kind of like a function hall. Outside that, stairs will lead u to the first floor where there is meditation hall, which is really good, with air-conditioning. There's now also a prasadham/annadhaanam distribution area above the temple separately, where u can sit and eat and is quite spacious too. The street in which the temple is located is still a very busy road and traffic piles up always. So one definitely has to plan parking about your vehicles be it bike or car in some other street or road and better walk to the temple instead. Overall one of the oldest and best Baba temples in the city.

Calm and peaceful place.
I think only in this temple,people can touch saibaba idol.I love this place especially because of this.
Thursday will be so much crowd.
And on terrace they will provide free food for all devotees.

Mylapore, a popular cultural hub and a notable neighborhood of Chennai is regarded as one of the oldest residential localities in the city. The name 'Mylapore' holds religious significance among the lovely local people and the region is the home of several historic and most visited religious sites. It is heavily crowded on Thursdays and during weekends

Ever thought of an evening in a temple? You get yummy hot prasadam. Only if there is a big crowd it's difficult getting a second helping !

Go here Thursday evening for the best prasad in town !

Nice place to pray and have darshan of Sai Baba. There is a meditation room on first floor for undisturbed peaceful prayer. There us big rush of devotees specially on Thursday and festivals. In the backside bhajan room one can sit and sing bhajans. Discourses are done in the left side room. Literature and bhajan CDs are also available in a shop. Visits to Shirdi is also organised from here. There is a separate shop for pooja saamagree and pooja items in the premises.
Most awesome place in the country. Divine and clean. Mind soothing place on Earth.
Visited lord's place for his blessings. A very powerful temple of lord Vishnu. Divine temple. Must visit for all.
Good prayer hall. Very peaceful & best for heart & soul. We can have easy dharsan as per the time schedule.

For a temple that receives about 100,000 people a day, this place is amazingly clean - I mean spic and span. There is constant cleaning. Well organized.  The process implemented for a lot of darshan may be rigid, but there is no other way to manage that many number of people. 
A model temple, that tries constantly to eliminate corruption, focuses on devotees experience.
I can write big stories about this place, but the top few are:
1. They serve free food over tens of thousands of people every day. Not some random food, but quality controlled.
2. It doesn't matter which cottage one stays, they are as clean as they can ever be.
3. The timing is very well organized.
4. Use of technology as much as they can.
Every time I visit this temple, the crowd jitters me a bit, but as soon as the 3 to 4 second darshan, the only thing that comes to my mind is when am I going to come back here.  Such is this temple.
Here God is works for money with great people,who are working for god,if you have money, you can get direct tharisanan,and you don't have they push you away 🙄

It’s a great temple to visit.! There are two to three  facilities to climb up the mountain. There is rope car and you can walk. There is rope train too. I have heard it . Prasad is something you get right outside the temple, near the terrace. You have to pay 💰 more money to sit in front of good which happens at evenings of few days of a week. There is parking lot down. There are two to three entrances for this temple. Apart from this, when you climb up, there are so many shops on the climbing path. It’s fun to climb up and climb down if the weather is not sunny. Keep your slippers in car is another advice I want to provide.

This temple is famous for Lord Murugan. Timings: 5:00 AM - 12:00 PM & 4:00 PM - 9:00 PM  Entry Fee: No entry fee. It is also believed that worshipping Lord Murugan here is as pious as praying to him at the original Palani temple. If someone is unable to visit the original abode, they can pay their respects here, and Murugan will bless them all the same. Vadapalani Murugan Temple has a rich history and an ornate architecture and is also enriched with people's faiths from all-over the country.

It's a small temple if you ask me. Okay good place to visit. Just have a look, pray and ciao. Nothing much to do there. Just observe the architecture and you'll be on your way to the next destination. The aiyaar can be rude, so keep your phones close to you when taking pictures. Almost got my phone confiscated.

Well maintained temple especially given the fact that there is huge influx of devotees. Cleanliness inside the temple is very good.

This is a special artsy place in Bulawayo City Centre. You must visit the artist studios where you get an intimate feel of the beautiful art work while it's been made. The store there also have wonderful paintings so it's a great place  to purchase gifts.

Very difficult rating for me. Food was great. Place not very clean. A little dusting, a fan, ready waiters and easy to move chairs to allow customers to sit well would greatly improve the place. So its a place with great potential just not being managed properly.
Artwork is superb and people vibe is good during exhibition nights on Wednesday .

Good range of books and an ambience to indulge in thumbing the eye catching titles, with a good spread of gadgetry and toys. Surprising to see decline in the range offered in diaries and calendars while a rise in generic stationary items. Highly trending in non fiction titles is another aspect of 2019 at landmark books arena.. Very encouraging changes in layout of stores, so that one feels like spending time there.

One of the best places to go to if you're a person who just loves spending your time amongst books. They have the perfect collection of books.. books of all categories.. also a comic book haven for comic book fans. They have a dedicated section when people can read books too. 
Apart from books, they have a wide collection of toys for children as well as action figures for collectibles and enthusiasts. 
Fashion accessories, unique forms of diaries, office supplies, bags, mugs, and chocolates are some of the other things that can be found here.

I had been to Landmark which is in Forum, it has developed over a timeframe as far as inside and quality also. Milestone is one stop arrangement on the off chance that you are a book significant other. You have all the assortment of books running from anecdotal, magazines, recorded, instructive and so forth. They have great assortment of books for children too, I like the flawless story books for them.

The games activity is likewise great and contains all the fundamental necessities for all the game. We had purchased a cycle from that point, the conveyance for which was entirely quick. A dazzling spot for book significant others.

Nice place to find books..... And you also get cute stuffs... Not to mention the toy section.... Oh boy!!! .... Doesn't matter how old I get, I will always go in there to check out those cute stuffed toys and marvel avenger figures!!

The shop is good. The collection of books and games is good ( online price is much cheaper). But the staff is untrained. They asked me debit card pin stating ATM machine under charging instead of asking cash as alternative. They did not serviced me to another queue for payment. The payment processing takes more than 30 minutes in queue. Very slow staff.

Excellent vegetarian restaurant.    Healthy food.   Hygienic preparations.     Affectionate service.     Worth for money.      Family atmosphere.      We can enjoy.     Highly safe to stomach.     Traditional varieties.     Strictly no deep fried items.
Those with a taste for traditional south Indian food will love it. Good service, a bit pricey, but yes it's different.. 4 stars for the service and ambience.. 3 stars for the food..

Kind service, wonderful healthy food and reasonable price.
If you ever heard about Ayurveda, or at least want to know how to eat properly, you should come!
Highly recommended

Restaurant is good. If you like organic food, then this is the must visit place.  You can't find even bottled water. You will get only herbal water which is good for health. You can find varieties of dosas all are in different taste.

This is very good vegetarian hotel. Any one has dislike for heavy spices laden food will like this place. Their lunch is absolutely a delight. They also serve dinner (Tiffin) which is mostly non white rice based dish which makes it much more healthier. This is place is for any one who is looking for healthier alternative

Very old but good restaurant. Food is delicious,  service is extremely good. 

In the midst of the bazaar,  Parking available as per availability.  Authenticity of food is maintained. 

Good stop over point along With family inside such crowded place. pricing is very moderate. 

Polite behavior and quick service of the staff is the core strength.

It is in a prime location. Needs improvement.  Once it was very popular. One of my favourite restaurants but now I haven't visited for long time since pulling power has been reduced.  Quality was good when I visited and taste too was good service was not bad but I missed something

Grand old vegetarian restaurant. Albeit food being decent the place looks run down. Lacks a sense of cleanliness. The attire of the service staff general upkeep of the place leaves much to be desired. Rhe Service was really very good. Excellent location and the food being decent is the only saving grace that keeps this place ticking. Looks like it's the beginning of the end!
Food Tarrifs are quite reasonable. Quality of Food served is good. Less Crowded. So, one can spend some time in the Restaurant. Hence, I would recommend. Thanks
A spacious restaurant. Has AC on 1st floor. At festival time they open more rooms. food is reasonably good.
They are one of the few restaurants that serve mini tiffin. It's good here. Ambience is low. Noisy. But the a/c hall is good.

Worst experience..rude behaviour of staff
Food is expensive and if you go there without change, you'll be in big trouble
very nice south indian restaurant.  part of a big chain. very clean environment. fast service. reasonable rates.

Food was ok as usual, service however was rushed and inattentive. Surprisingly, their filter coffee  was not memorable. They have a rest room here which is convenient, although I can't say it was well maintained.
Overall the food was good.. Staff was friendly.. But a bit pricey for the quantity..
Not Soo good but you can taste once

Budget MRP. Food is worthy for that price tag. Taste of the food not above average.
1. There is no separate washroom for ladies. 
2. Staff response is OK. 
3. Order serving time also quick.
4. Overall good for friends not for people who look for privacy.
Nice place,  reasonable price, more variety of foods.
Taste of the food here is good and also cheap. Located opposite to Express avenue mall.
Fairly decent place. Parking is tough because it's right beside Express Avenue. Food is tasty enough. Pricing is moderate. We've been regular there. Seveice is fast though!
Awesome place. Nice food and quality. A bit busy though
One of the famous among best place for quality sweets and snacks. Good customer service and maintenance. Need to improve the parking facilities.
Amazing experience and service. They served us so much there was no space in our stomach, intestine or even mouth
Yummy north Indian food and sweets. Would definitely recommend
Quality speaks here...Try once a different food..Best in city.. Strongly recommend.

So when you aim at taste one of oldest and still a best place to dine. But in case of cost its little high.. Sambhar idly is very famous and delicious too. Cost of 2 idly is 47 normal and inside AC its 67..

Its one of the locality known long time, tried a tea and my friend had a coffee. He said its very established in service and taste.

I've not grasped much insight but the tea was good enough to say the shop functions as described

Just visited the place today morning (new year) between 11-11:30am and seated near the table at TAKE ORDER. Heavily crowded.
At the end of service, the waiter who served us asked for total of Rs 282 with bill on his hand and not given to us and tried to give a impression that he  is in a rush. 
Sounded suspicious as it was only two of us with a kid. When demanded to hand over the bill, it was only Rs 182.  Rip off!!!
To the Management - pay attention to the ethics of your servers.
To the customers - make it a point to verify the bill before you pay especially if it is crowded..
Thought I would register my experience so nobody gets ripped off in the bill here. Quality is good as usual.
The worst hotel, I have ever seen. The price was too high but there is no worth for it.....and that place is also not popular place, that is only triplicane....
You want to eat the famous Idly-Sambar, this is the only place where you will get it. Like ONLY PLACE. This is the trademark of Chennai!!
People will sit on your head during peak hours and you can't eat peacefully. Just eat and get away ASAP.  Food quality is good. Ambience 2 star. Food 5 star. Average 3.
Had mini combo breakfast. It's worth for money. Only 40Rs. Quality and quantity also good. But they missed to serve my compliment mini coffee.
Good for budget vegetarianers. Pro you get variety tasty veg dishes. Con if you are a frequent visitor make sure you tip well else service goes bad.
Tasty food overall but gets crowded so quickly. Takeouts can be made better.

The location is in a busy area and space available to park only two wheelers. But they serve tasty South Indian dishes. North Indian delicacies are not upto the mark. Their mini breakfast for RS.40+ GST is good. They have an AC hall in the first floor. Service is okay. One of the good South Indian hotel in Anna Nagar.

Authentic taste and prompt service. Car parking is available. The biriyani is very good. Haven't had an opportunity to try any other food as yet but will surely update the review after my second visit. Conveniently located on Cathedral road opposite music academy, you cant miss it.
Not so great. It's meant for taste. That's always good. Service becomes poor day by day. Being Sunday evening they had only one order taker
Their food is amazing. It is supposed to be much better for non vegetarians. Being a vegetarian I still enjoyed their food. Perfect Andhra meals!
Great place at Chennai for Andhra cuisine. The veg meals is highly recommended. The adjacent bakery offers great variety of Andhra delicacies.
Typical Andhra food quality was very good. We had veg meals, oil was less and was tasty. Car parking is available with valet services as well.
Food quality 👌👌👌👌 cleanliness 4.5star staffs excellent behaviour
Very very nice person in tamilnadu.  Thanks
The Greater.Hotel...Respecting Jayalalitha..Amma
For old and poor people this heaven, taste is more than what u pay
Excellent service
Great traditional South Indian food. Good ambience. Would have been better if they had some live singing or music performances in the traditional Southern states style as well
Love the ambience here. Would recommend this 100%. Food s very tasty. Perfect south indian food. Costly but worth it.
Best place for South Indian curry. Excellent ambience and friendly staff. Only downside is comes with a price tag
I have been hear form 2002 and its a delight the servings and the food hits the mark every time and the ambiance has changed in a tone which we will not be able to notice.
Food, ambience and service is top notch. I think they just need to add variety to the menu otherwise everything was great.
Good service provider for chimneys  we often use them to service elica chimneys in issues
Avadimarket.blogspot. com

Good and fast service. Fried spring rolls and fried wanton great for starters. Various soup are very tasty. Main course with fried seafood noodles n fried rice with ginger chicken, fried fish and stir fried vege are perfect. Fanciful names for Ice cream for dessert are fabulous. Crab claws is a must have item.
Not an ordinary Chinese restaurant. Crab claws, vegetable wanton, roast pork with pepper, some of the must-try dishes.  One of the few family restaurants which serves alcohol.
I am visiting this Chinese for about 35 years.. the same taste exists... till date... Try the Crab Claws & Crispy Fried chicken

This used to be a nice place. No longer. The food is pretty bad..the service is dismal..
 I went there after one year.. and would never go there again ...

This is a family favourite. Have been brought up on the food here.  Lovely chilly beef,  prawn pepper salt,  crispy fried wantow,  manchow soup and pan fried noodles!  It is on the pricey side but a good place for family!

Best customer service ever I received.. Such an awesome place to have chettinad foods, simple, affordable price & varieties in non-veg dosa's are magnificent. The set-up is good to feel like natural scenary.
Great service and pakka South Indian dishes
Great place to eat

Not much to write home about but I struggled to find the USP of this restaurant. Mexican food not to everyone's taste. Kryptos Willi does it much better. Neither costly nor cheap. That's it. Oh! one thing I always find about all restaurants in Chennai that you'll be blown away with their quality of service and staff behaviour. Chennai restaurateurs has hit the sweet spot.

3.5 out of 5. Taste is good and cost is bit high but acceptable for the place. Good ambience. The main dining area is like siting in the middle of a garden as it is surrounded by trees, plants. One should visit in the evening time as some of the dishes are not available during lunch time. Car parking is fine. Staff are good. Rest rooms are just ok. Cleanliness of the surrounding is 2.5 out of 5. They got a good place but maintenance is not up to the mark.

Poor quality of food. 
The ambiance might have been better if it's maintained well! 
Pathetic service and the pets are not even maintained properly and also not sure if they even feed the cats.

Felt like entering into am entirely different world surrounded with lush greens and cute creatures. There's a hut of cute bunnies, a house of various cat breeds, a room full of pigeons, ducks and emu too!!!

And the food- the best in taste and quantity. Totally a treat for the eyes and tummy! Totally awesome experience. That too the location is in ECR, which means a place to hangout and eat after a drive! 

Must visit place in Chennai!
Nice restaurant, not only the taste but the environment. You can feed doves, see rabits, Emu's, and kids may enjoy a lot.. nice place to put up for couple of hours.

Not a pocket friendly restaurant. But they have kids attractive zones like pigeons (100s of pigeons) rabbits, Emu & Cats and you can allow the kids to feed the rabbits and pigeons. piegons are really cool to feed as they will come n sit on Ur hands to take the feed. Kids will love it

This is one of the best barbecue in chennai i have ever visited.. The ambience was so good and staffs were super friendly.. i would suggest to try this location in groups.. My friends and family really enjoyed their lunch here.. If your planning to visit in the weekends better reserve table with the head counts this place is usually crowded during weekends.. :)👍

One of the best place to fulfill our lunch and dinner with friends. Lot of varieties available. Can't taste all of them. Evening is the best time to enjoy and spend time with your belongings. DJ music mixer is good and enjoyable. Such a good place. Parking facilities are good. Customer service and maintenance is very good.

Had a wonderful experience being here, food was great, ambient was good and overall the service and hospitality of the staffs were to the fullest..! Had tried similar themed restaurant all around the city but still BN Stands out from the crowd with very good hospitality and food taste..!! Definitely a must go place..!
Had a great and full stomach lunch. Veg option was good. The corn fry is everyone's favorite. Loved all the dishes and had an opportunity to make my own omelette and loved it

Worst service. Ok food. Refilling was pretty bad. Staff who do not accept that things are won't. 

Best part, go as a crowd loose choice on the welcome drink. They might give u options but will get u what ever they like.

There are much barbecue places than this one.
Has lost its authenticity..... would love to see more authentic chettinadu recipes on the menu... no value for money

I checked in zomato for ratings and menu before deciding to go there. The menu at the restaurant was entirely different and priced differently, good thing was that it was less priced. I ordered fish meals, and the fish curry was really good.
A decent place to have food at decent prices and royal ambiance.

Taste wise I'm felt really good. But when we visited the restaurant by 3.30 where in the timing till 4. Most of the items were not available. The waiter asked me to take plain rice with some gravy. Plain rice quantity also very less and the gravy quantity was very poor.

Excellent food and service. We ordered a prawn biryani with mutton chukka and chicken varuval. All items were very tasty. I also had a kulfi for dessert which really topped everything else. Highly recommended.
So good!! Excellent food and great service. The coffee is also amazing.
Very tasty and traditional.. excellent service ..but now days food  quality not good. Unsatisfied

Idly alone is soft. Side dishes like sambar and they provided 4 types of chutney. None of them were up to the mark. Ambience is not that good, felt some foul smell may be from AC. Waiter was not responsive. Smpliy they are spoiling the name of Murugan Idly shop.
Good idli and podi idli.. tasty sweet pongal.. with best filter coffee...

The one at ormes road and the one at Tnagar are the best ones I have seen. Dosa variety, idly variety, pongal, vada are at it's best. They have consistently given good food for many yrs now. I visit almost every week. Food is served in banana leaf.
Like the ambience. The food was good too. North Indian breads were really expensive though.
like the ambiance, like a pirate.. and reasonably good food.. good work by the owners..
The theme is good but the food and the service does not meet the expectations

It's no more the OLD RANGIS it used to be. It used to be so good for pork and beef. Now it's so famous for OILY FOOD and when you speak to the supervisor about the quality of the food. He just smiles at you like you're appreciating him

One of the oldest and Best Chinese restaurant in Town. You can go with a shallow pocket.
Food quality and quantity are excellent.
Good food at affordable price with low wait times.

A really tiny place in the middle of the city which retains its own regular customers. Tiny = only 8 tables. Food provided is commendable and absolutely no issues if you're a non-vegetarian. No restroom but still a decent place with car/bike park. Overall 4*
My love for this place never fades. Quiet and peaceful joint for awesome food at an awesome price.

My only regret was that I didn't try this restaurant until the final days of my trip. Great experience. Food was outstanding. Reasonably priced. Encouraged to eat with your hands although you can request utensils.

Definitely not worth.... Had a lot of expectations from this place and this place is not even inch close to what we expected ... Staff showed no interest to explain the menu or pay attention to our ask... Service was very slow... Seating options are not comfortable... Only thing that's comparable to their 5* status was its bill.... 7 of us were there for corporate dinner and returned with nothing but disappointment....

Food is good, ambience was  OK.... But nothing standing out to give you the WOW experience. First shocking point was no spoons forks... Have to dine with hands! OOPS... Took along a few US delegates with me for the lunch...and ended up requesting them to eat the food with hands...it's really tough to eat large chunks of meat...with hands..without cutting them into smaller chunks.... Guys, please highlight this point when customers are doing the reservation!!!
Super amazing food..from heaven. Always taste.the same. I wish i could cook just one dish that they do. My guilty pleasure
A place can't be worst that this. A road side shop has better food and better service. Arrogant dumb staff. Food can't get any worse. Please learn from road side shops

Frankly I had never been to a Mainland China before. But this place made me wished why didn't I do that. We had ordered Noodles and Rice, exotic vegetable gravy and spring rolls. Everything tasted really good. Service was excellent. The ambience serves as a really nice place to go for a lunch/dinner with family.

A great place for a team lunch or family outing. They have buffet at reasonable rates every day if the week.  Situated in church landing road it is easily accessible from most of the parts of the city.  The metro exit extends right into the road.  It is a one way and would be better to reach there in an auto or car

The buffet was simply completely off the mark. They had 3 non vegetarian starters, a main course with non vegetarian gravies - you need to have then with veg fried rice or noodles. 

I would have been fine if the starters tasted very good but it was not the case. A fish starter was good but none of the others. Now for the reason for 2 stars Ave not less... Their ice tea was fantastic and all my colleagues agreed their cocktails were nice. Another star because they asked for our feedback and got some prawns that tasted nice.

I suggest you skip the buffet here. Not worthy of 900+ per head.

First time to mainland China.. eye soothing decor, peaceful ambience.. delicious food.. courteous service.. but kept asking feedback for every dish served which kinda bothered.. hence a star less from 5.. overall fine dine experience by leaders..

I had always heard the hype about Mainland China but had not got a chance to try for so many years. So finally couple of weeks back we dropped in here for lunch unplanned. Luckily we got the table without having to wait. 

So we took buffet lunch & starters were served on table. I loved the fish in starters & chicken was also nice. In veg there was potato & corn dishes which was ok. Few beverages were part of buffet & I took lime juice which was very strong lime juice, definitely good when having buffets(for diet conscious !! ) :P Jokes apart !! next took the main course chicken fried rice was authentically Chinese which I had not tasted else where. Also other dishes were authentic Chinese saucy dishes which was tasty & great Chinese food. Dessert section had the mousses, cakes & ice creams which was the usual ones. I was hoping to see some Chinese desserts which would make it a complete Chinese food ! At the end they gave a Chinese tea which was good too!

Ambiance is great & loved the interior decors. Cost for food was worth it.

A historical building right in town. Has a lot of photos of the past and history. Royalty has stayed here. This was the Spring Flower Show and they had the CWA serving Devonshire tea, which they do once a month.

This restaurant is located a little away from the heart of Chennai city near the beach of kottivakkam. I had gone to this place twice and all I can say is this place has my heart .The ambience is very romantic and it is certainly the best restaurant for a quite lovely candle light date night .Coming to the food the pizzas are absolutely amazing and the steak is also delicious.You should definitely try those .The staff is extremely courteous and friendly.They were also professional and we did not have to wait for the food.However being a student I felt the prices are a bit heavy on the pocket but it is totally worth the bucks!

Food:5/5
Staff:5/5
Service:5/5
Ambience:5/5
Location:4/5
Price:4/5

Nice place to try real Italian dishes in Chennai. Please be open to new variety of dishes and don't expect Indian style to alone with the dishes. This place serves nice food and the ambience of this place is great as it is close to the beach and also it's a lawn restaurant.

This is a beautifully and tastefully conceived restaurant but there is a lot more to go in terms of matching up to the expectations that one forms when one walks into Bella Ciao! Maybe because it was a particularly busy evening when we visited the place, a party of four, or probably because it was the weekend, but the food was really late - easily more than an hour since the order was taken!  Just the fact that the food was served late probably might be misleading in arriving at a conclusion that the food was not all that great, but like I said, it is just a misleading thought - the food was very tasty.  They sure could have avoided the delay, but frankly speaking, I will visit there again to give the place a second look.

Food was awesome. Very neatly maintained, great ambiance. Light and non-spicy food. Loved the salad and pizza which I ordered for my son. Never seen him finish the entire pizza anywhere else. Service was great. Its right next to the beach and could go to the beach after having food. Slightly expensive but was overall worth it. Would love to go back again.

One of the best Italian in the adyar / Thiruvanmiyur area. Nice cozy setup. Good ambience. Quiet place. Close to beach. All this makes this a great place for a great evening dinner..the staff here are friendly and go great lengths to make sure the guests are happy. Yummy food. Quite well presented.

Don't order from here as if you fall asleep you don't get your order or your money back so please don't order from little Italy pizza really bad review go to pizza hut as its a lot better than this place

I moved out of Aberdeen a year ago and what a loss it is not to have Little Italy around.. I simply cannot find a pizza restaurant with the same quality pizzas as this.

Expand! And for every newcomers, I highly recommend the Little Italy Calzone 12" if you like a bit spicy food!
Their sizes are a bit on the small side but otherwise great value for your money.

I went and ordered food throigh their website. The order was rejected due to them being too busy which I totally understand. However they proceeded to charge me twice and took the money out of my account. I emailed them and have not received any response. I am really not happy with this and this is slmesomet that people need to be avare off

The pizza is very good. I would say 7/10. I have tried the piri piri one and calzone. The number of ingredients in calzone is perfect. No option to order garlic sauce. Only garlic mayo available which taste very average. It is so easy to make garlic sauce, it should be a problem for the pizza place. The delivery time was shocking, 1:35, during the week. I cannot imagine waiting time during the peak times. Furthermore, the place is quite dear. It is not real Italian pizza therefore price should be lower. Why do I need to pay extra fee while ordering online through your website. I see the potential but some changes must be done.
Very Good restaurant and awesome food and aumbience..
Posch.  Excellent wine

I hope I am the first and the last one to rate this place. 

At first, we were asked to seat in the corner of the restaurant with no one coming to attend us for next ten minutes. 

Our waiter for the day - Prasanna was not at all the knowledgable on the menu. He didn't even bring the Drinks menu to us in the first place. After we insisted, he got us just one menu, seeing there are two people on the table.

We wanted to have Old Fashioned and Prasanna had no idea what that drink was. We were later informed that the restaurant ran out of bitter. How can a hotel like Taj run out of bitter ?  We settled for Kingfisher Beer. 

The dinner started off in a very disappointing way when we were served some tasteless Anitpasti that can only be compared to Corn Fluid. The Main Course tasted equally bad.

For the main course, I ordered a Spaghetti and I made pretty clear that I my pasta needs to be a Spaghetti but I was served Linguine. Again, there was no communication in terms of how our food and our experience was. Moreover, our waiter got us one plate and kept the other guest waiting for next ten minutes. In a restaurant, you always get two plates together. That's restaurant 101. 

This was very disappointing experience. And, I was charged Rs 3600 for this experience. We left the food on the plate and walked away and no one even enquired about that. 

If you still wanna go to this place. Be my guest.

Teppan as a Japanese restaurant was once the pinnacle and the best place for Japanese food in Chennai.
Unfortunately as time has gone by they have fallen far from where they once were.
“How far the might have fallen”.

The issues :
1. The first item tuna sashimi 
- the tunas picture in the menu is misleading 
(Red)
Where as what actually comes is a “supposed purple” but turns out to be brown .
- the tuna itself was brittle and crumbling 
The arrangement slapped together 
And the cut was sloppy sloppy sloppy
2.salmon sashimi despite complaining about the tuna 
Was tough for salmon
And the portion was like 4 edamame piece slices
3 

Positives
The temaki was nicely sized 
But expensive 
Good taste as well
And the samurai maki was just decent.

It also isn’t the fact of availablilty of meats and ingredients at affordable prices as other restaurants have had no problems running and succeeding , at an even cheaper cost than teppan.

I don’t mean to insult teppan or the staff but I really felt that it has lost its flair

I hope that this is seen and acted on in a manner that would help the restaurant.

Unfortunately I haven’t tried the live counter so I have based my views on the main starters and popular foods.

Typical Americanised Japanese restaurant
The kind of place where you enjoy the chef juggling and burning stuff.

Food taste was very monotonous and junky and not professional, just like any other American stuff.
Any decent person would notice hot metal plate cooking will ruin the delicate taste of sushi.
It may be fun if your young and your with a bunch of friends, but not the place to come if you want Japanese food.
Who would expect a teppan restaurant without Okonomiyaki?

I am a fish lover and this place was heaven for me. Had sushi and simply loved it! My dad once brought a packed vegetarian sea weed soup from Japan while he was on his research visit. The restaurant served me the exact soup here as well. I liked it very much!
I love teppan! I have come here so many times, that I have lost count! Love the veg sushis, and garlic fried rice. Also the prawn tempura! Yum
Very nice Japanese food, but then again, what would I know? It's not like I'm Japanese

Nicely built apartments. Stilt plus four. Ample free space , parking space and  good cross ventilation. Quite place away from the hustle and bustle yesterday just off the highway. Access is a bit round about , but since there is no traffic it's not an issue.

This place is good and calm. It is located on highway other side of mogappair & nolambur. While entering to Casagrand Cedars, we need to go through "Mass,rough,dirty" industries with short road. No hospitals / showrooms in this area.  For anything (except groceries), we need to cross highway and should go to mogappair.

Casagrand cedars is a residential apartments in Ayanambakkam. The flats here are of 2bhk and 3bhk. The cost are slightly affordable for a middle and higher middle class people. Amenities available. Parking is quite ok. Transit available.
Great apartment in the area. The best community in ayanambakkam
Too expensive for the location
Good ambience, comfortable rooms and guest services 👌
One of the worst buffet dinner. Very limited menu, but it is not worth for the cost. There is no finishing touch.  Mg should give spl attention to the menu.
Went for lunch buffet. A lot of good variety of food but food was average.
We had a great food at entree, apriciate the entire team
excellent service and excellent location.
Dresses are good. But not worth for so much cost. Not so much variety of dresses.
All time favourite. Vast collections at affordable price. All under one roof. So all my needs are met always.
Really good collection. I always find good stuff for my family.. Very nice location..

Brand new collections with ethnicity. Good customer service even they didn't close the shop after working hours.Staffs were very friendly and polite.Great place for unique collections and styles be it for both men and women.you can also find both traditional and trendy dresses with good offers and designs.place that is to be never missed for uniqueness.
Good  collection for women's. Little bit costly. You can find trendy and decent outfits  in this boutique.
Food and ambience very much below expectation. Should improve on both count. Hospitality was good. But what is the use of hospitality without good food?
Nice ambience and well connected. Good was ok. Nothing extraordinary though
Great food and amazing ambience. But take care of the prices since its a bit costly

Ok'ish. Ambience was a let down. Expected something but turned out to be an ordinary (like every other). The name and ambience dont have anything in common. Food was ordinary and the service too. The restaurant was cramped up with tables as if they wanted squeeze every inch. I wouldn't be visiting a Copper Chimney again as there is not much to enjoy here.

You want to elevate your taste buds with some yummy lip smacking food, then get in and order their kebabs and pot dum Biryani. Their kebabs are perfectly grilled and mildly spiced. The pot biryanis will slide and the taste will last longer. I could personally finish one whole serve. Well enough boasting, you might have to taste to catch my hype. There is valet parking. Prices are on the higher side but worth the fine dine ambience and superior quality food.

Very nice gated community. Perfect plan in construction and ample free space includes two small parks and a badminton court. Well maintained and newly painted apartment. I am a proud owner of a Flat here.
Good and clean place to live. No pets allowed. Tap water is sometimes dirty and generator facility does not work sometimes.. otherwise it's peaceful.. All good to rent

Nice and secured with play area. We usually go here to our friend's house. This place has two children play areas. One located near the entrance on the left near guest parking area, which has 2 swings; 1 slide ; 1 sit-go-round; couple of benches for the people to sit.  The other one is located at the end while entering the apartment. It's inside a small park. It contains swings, slide, see saw etc. It also has a badminton court where you can play with appropriate shoes.

I stayed here for 3 years.  Well maintained by the Secretary.  Security,  Cleaning staff and electrical and plumbing people  are perfect in their jobs.  Car parking is also good.  All Ground floors of all 7 blocks are left for parking. Almost, every flat has a parking place. 
   External re-painting  is being done now for all blocks,  as part of maintainence. Recently a good fountain and shuttle court are made in Park. NK

The apartment is very well connected to the highway by bus and Auto. The residents are very helpful and cooperative. It's already 10 years but the building looks really new. The environment specially the park is very clean and well maintained. The security here is really good.

Was very impressed! Good food, great for sharing. Highly suggest getting three or four items and sharing. Our friends like the yogurt drinks. 
Bonus, they have a great yard that our kids could all run around in and we can watch them form the tables.
A good place for Asian foods.

The best Indian food that I've had in all of east Africa.  Service was friendly and fast! The waiters were very quick to refill drinks.  Dinner in most other restaurants took about 2.5hrs. As a party of four here, we were served within 20 minutes and were done within 1hr 30.  We ended up eating here twice because it was so good.
Best restaurant in the world. I’m drooling now just thinking about it. Fast service, good food, friendly staff.
The food smell so good!! 👌

their shop at grand Mall is very small. but the collections were kind of different. not visited their main shop on 100ft road yet. but for sure next time we come to Chennai.

recommend places
Good price and variety for ladies.
Great traditional South Indian food. Good ambience. Would have been better if they had some live singing or music performances in the traditional Southern states style as well
Love the ambience here. Would recommend this 100%. Food s very tasty. Perfect south indian food. Costly but worth it.
Best place for South Indian curry. Excellent ambience and friendly staff. Only downside is comes with a price tag
I have been hear form 2002 and its a delight the servings and the food hits the mark every time and the ambiance has changed in a tone which we will not be able to notice.
Food, ambience and service is top notch. I think they just need to add variety to the menu otherwise everything was great.
